cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with visual search. It may also belong to Information Retrieval (cs.IR) as it involves searching for categories based on queries. Machine Learning (cs.LG) is another likely sub-category as the paper introduces a new approach for mapping examples to a common semantic space. Multimedia (cs.MM) is also possible as the paper deals with visual domains. Finally, Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) is a less likely sub-category as the paper does not explicitly deal with language, but it may be relevant if the search queries involve text.
